      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED BROOK (1) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, hitting the frame latest when 2nd at this track over 300m. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Winning claims. SHE'S SEEKING (6) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at Hobart over 340m behind Zari Exact (19.81) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Won at her only start from this box. Has ability and is one of the better chances. QUIRKY NACHO (2) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Gunnedah over 340m behind Go Forward Blaze (20.95) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Has never missed the frame from three starts from this draw, including a win. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. FEDERAL JOKER (8) will be hard to beat despite making his debut at this circuit.",
